  <h1 id="terms-of-service-title">Terms of Service</h1>
  <p>
    By using the service provided on the GTmetrix.com website's ("Service"), a
    service of GTmetrix, you are agreeing to be bound by the following terms
    and conditions ("Terms of Service"). Please read the following carefully to
    ensure you understand the conditions of your use of the service.
  </p>

  <h3>GTmetrix Account Usage</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>GTmetrix may not be used for and illegal or abusive activities. Doing
    so will result in the termination of your GTmetrix account.</li>
    <li>Password security is the responsibility of the user.</li>
    <li>You are limited to one GTmetrix account per person or business.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>API/API Credit Usage</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>The GTmetrix API is provided “as is” and “as available”.</li>
    <li>The API may be modified by GTmetrix at any time.</li>
    <li>GTmetrix reserves the right to limit the amount of API requests in
    cases of overuse or abuse of the API.</li>
    <li>GTmetrix reserves the right to restrict accounts or IP addresses which
    overuse or abuse the API.</li>
    <li>GTmetrix reserves the right to determine what constitutes overuse or
    abuse of the API.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Billing</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>You must provide and maintain accurate billing information. Subscribing
    to a paid GTmetrix account gives GTmetrix license to charge you and/or bill
    your credit card for GTmetrix related fees, as well as any applicable
    taxes.</li>
    <li>Payments will be charged in advance on the first day of each billing
    cycle for that cycle.</li>
    <li>Subscription fees will be charged automatically unless you cancel your
    service.</li>
    <li>You can change between different billing cycles at any time. By
    default, if you are downgrading your plan, the new billing cycle length
    will take effect after the expiration of the current cycle (i.e. at the
    next renewal date). Plan upgrades take affect immediately. See Changing
    Account Types point 4 for information on immediate downgrades.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Changing Account Types</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>You may upgrade or downgrade your GTmetrix account at any time from the
    GTmetrix PRO tab. An upgrade is any plan where the cost per billing cycle
    is greater than or equal to your current plan's cost per billing cycle. All
    plan changes which are not upgrades are considered downgrades.</li>
    <li>After an upgrade you will be billed immediately for the remaining time
    until the next renewal. This bill will be pro-rated in accordance with the
    amount you have already paid.</li>
    <li>After a downgrade you will be billed at the new rate on the next
    renewal date.</li>
    <li>If you wish to downgrade immediately, you may shift to any plan of
    equal or lesser value than the pro-rated amount remaining on your
    current billing cycle.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Refund Policy</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>No refunds or exchanges on subscription services, except as assessed on
    a case-by-case basis. To request a refund, e-mail
    <a href="mailto:billing@gtmetrix.com">billing@gtmetrix.com</a> within 7
    days (one week) of the payment date stating the reason for your
    request.</li>
    <li>If you do not receive this receipt e-mail it is your responsibility to
    contact GTmetrix within these 7 days via e-mail to confirm that GTmetrix
    has received your request.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Cancellation and Termination of Service</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>You may at any time cancel your paid subscription by downgrading to the
    free GTmetrix account, provided that any past invoices have been paid. This
    can be done inside the GTmetrix control panel.  GTmetrix does not accept
    cancellations via e-mail or phone.</li>
    <li>Any abuse of the Service will lead to termination of your account.
    GTmetrix reserves the right to decide what is considered abuse of the
    Service.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Changes to Terms of Service</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>These Terms of Service may be changed without prior notice.  The
    current Terms of Service can be viewed at:
    <a href="http://gtmetrix.com/terms-of-service.html">http://gtmetrix.com/terms-of-service.html</a></li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Disclaimer</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>The GTmetrix Service is provided “as is” and “as available”.</li>
    <li>GTmetrix reserves the right to add to, remove, and otherwise modify its
    services, including features, paid account types and fees.</li>
    <li>GTmetrix reserves the right to discontinue the Service at any time
    after a 30-day notice via e-mail.</li>
    <li>GTmetrix reserves the right to change the prices for the Service and
    any connected extra services at any time.</li>
    <li>GTmetrix gives no warranties regarding the correctness of the data
    collected with the Service or any potential corruption or loss of such
    data.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Limitation of Liability</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>You expressly understand and agree that GTmetrix shall not be liable
    for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, consequential or exemplary
    damages, including but not limited to, damages for loss of profits,
    goodwill, use, data or other intangible losses (even if GTmetrix has been
    advised of the possibility of such damages), resulting from: 1. the use or
    the inability to use the GTmetrix service; 2. the cost of procurement of
    substitute goods and services resulting from any goods, data, information
    or services purchased or obtained or messages received or transactions
    entered into through or from the GTmetrix service; 3.  unauthorized access
    to or alteration of your transmissions or data; 4. statements or conduct of
    any third party on the GTmetrix service; or 5. any other matter relating to
    the GTmetrix service.</li>
    <li>Any decisions or claims you make based on data from the GTmetrix
    Service are your sole responsibility. GTmetrix shall not be held liable for
    any such decisions or claims.</li>
    <li>In no event shall GTmetrix’s total liability to you for all
    damages, losses, and causes of action (whether in contract, tort
    (including, but not limited to, negligence), or otherwise) exceed the
    amount paid by you, if any, for accessing this site.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Indemnification</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>You agree to indemnify, defend and hold harmless GTmetrix and its
    officers, directors, employees, consultants and agents from any and all
    third party claims, liability, damages and/or costs (including, but not
    limited to, attorney fees) arising from your use of the GTmetrix service,
    your violation of the terms of use or your infringement, or infringement by
    any other user of your account, of any intellectual property or other right
    of any person or entity.</li>
    <li>You agree to immediately notify GTmetrix of any unauthorized use of
    your account or any other breach of security known to you.</li>
  </ol>

